# 5. Acceptance Criteria

### AC-1
Mandatory connections must be validated before Fetch Stories.

### AC-2
Connection status must be visible using user-friendly indicators.

### AC-3
Libraries must be visually distinguished and excluded from deployment-specific validations.

### AC-4
Previous Release Version must resolve using Kubernetes → Existing Logic → Manual Selection.

### AC-5
Production deployment metadata must be captured and persisted.

### AC-6
Only one reusable Kubernetes metadata service shall exist.

### AC-7
Existing Release comparison logic must remain intact.

### AC-8
Production Git Commit SHA must be collected and used as a deployment anchor.

### AC-9
Release Branch and Production metadata must both participate in commit analysis.

### AC-10
Main branch commits after Release Branch creation must be analyzed for Release Stories.

### AC-11
Missing commits belonging to Release Stories shall be reported as violations.

### AC-12
Cherry-picks, direct release commits, squash merges, and rebases shall be handled where possible.

### AC-13
Fallback commit history search shall be configurable.

### AC-14
Only Release Story commits shall participate in validation.

### AC-15
Commit SHA shall be the primary business identifier.

### AC-16
Imported Git metadata shall refresh correctly.

### AC-17
Manual overrides, approvals, comments, and audit history shall never be lost during refresh.

### AC-18
Removed commits shall be marked instead of immediately deleted.

### AC-19
Commit validation history shall be preserved independently of imported metadata.

### AC-20
Issue Type shall be fetched, persisted, and displayed using compact standard icons with hover text.

### AC-21
Every violation shall have a category, detailed explanation, and recommended resolution.

### AC-22
Hovering over the information icon shall clearly explain the violation and recommended action.

### AC-23
Reactive parallel processing shall be used wherever beneficial to improve performance.

### AC-24
Execution timing logs shall be available for all major operations.

### AC-25
A Kubernetes research document shall accompany the implementation.

### AC-26
The implementation shall remain fully backward compatible until the new production-based approach has been validated and explicitly approved for replacing the existing logic.

